#{\footnote\pard\plain Sound dialog}
K{\footnote\pard\plain sounddlgHelp}
${\footnote\pard\plain Help for Sound dialog}
\pard\plain\f0\fs20
Select {\b Sound} to activate sound for events.
\par The events list contains the names of all events you can assign sounds to.
\par The sounds list contains the names of all available sound files as well as an entry <No sound> and
<Beep>. To assign a sound to an event, select the event first and then double-click on the
sound that you want to assign.
\par Use the {\b Volume} slider to set the sound volume.
\par The {\b Play (>)} button plays the currently selected sound.
\par The {\b OK} button closes the Sound dialog and the changed settings
become active.
\par The {\b Cancel} button closes the Sound dialog. Any changes that were made
are discarded.
\page

